  "golfP6": (()=>{const fn=(ctx) => {const { normalize: _normalize } = ctx;return _normalize(["After breakfast we will leave Baku for Gobustan Historical Reserve (65 km far). The reserve is a national historical landmark of Azerbaijan established to preserve the prehistoric rock carvings, mud volcanoes and musical stones in the region. Before the start of the tour around Gobustan we will visit the interactive museum with the same name, where with the help of special programs and multimedia touch screens we will get information about the nature, the flora of Gobustan. Gobustan was inscribed in the UNESCO World Heritage List in 2007. Azerbaijan has the highest number of mud volcanoes in the world. In the afternoon visit Heydar Aliyev Cultural Center (closed on Mondays). The building was designed by worldwide recognized Iraqi-British architect and Pritzker Prize winner Zaha Hadid in 2012. "])};fn.source="After breakfast we will leave Baku for Gobustan Historical Reserve (65 km far). The reserve is a national historical landmark of Azerbaijan established to preserve the prehistoric rock carvings, mud volcanoes and musical stones in the region. Before the start of the tour around Gobustan we will visit the interactive museum with the same name, where with the help of special programs and multimedia touch screens we will get information about the nature, the flora of Gobustan. Gobustan was inscribed in the UNESCO World Heritage List in 2007. Azerbaijan has the highest number of mud volcanoes in the world. In the afternoon visit Heydar Aliyev Cultural Center (closed on Mondays). The building was designed by worldwide recognized Iraqi-British architect and Pritzker Prize winner Zaha Hadid in 2012. ";return fn;})(),
